@NODE "What"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}ToCopy.rexx - What Is It?@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}

I develop the script for friend, he is all way copying whole floppy to a directory on his 
harddrive.  This meant that opus directory was locked up in copying.  If he had to do 
anything else in file management, he had to load another copy into the amiga system.  
This was wasteful in computer resources.


What do I need

You need to have already installed ARexx on your system.  As well as the copy 
command in C directory which is part of your Dos system, and director opus
programmes version 4.12.


To install the ARexx script.

I've enclosed example of how to do this as an opus directory V4.12 configuration file.  
You will find it on Button labelled Tocopy of how to set up.  And a gif image of the
configuration screen setting up opus to run ToCopy.rexx script.


A bit more information on installing

The line which activate the ARexx script.  First call up the ARexx interpreter 
which then giving by parameter the storage location to call ToCopy.rexx programme.

In opus you most marked the list of options:-

Run asynchronously

All other settings are set to default.
 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}ToCopy.rexx - Requirements@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
To use ToCopy.rexx you will need:-

- AmigaDOS/Workbench 3.0 or higher (Does anyone still use WB 2.0 or earlier?)

- copy command in C directory

- ARexx installed on your system

- Dopus directory version 4.12
 
To the best of my knowledge ToCopy.rexx will work on @{B}ANY @{UB}Amiga
equipped with AmigaDOS/Workbench 3.0 or higher.


@ENDNODE

@NODE "How"

@{JCENTER}@{B}@{U}ToCopy.rexx - How To Use It@{UB}@{UU}
@{JLEFT}
@{B}@{U}Installation Script@{UB}@{UU}:-

@{B}@{U} multi-command move or copy @{UB}@{UU}:-


This might be included in a future version.

@{B}@{U}Manual Installation@{UB}@{UU}:-

1. Copy "ToCopy.rexx" into your assigned Rexx: directory.

2. Copy the file "ToCopy.Guide" to wherever you like to keep your
   documents.

3.  I've enclosed example of how to do this as an opus directory V4.12 
configuration file.  You will find it on Button labelled Tocopy of how to 
set up.  And a gif image of the configuration screen setting up opus to 
run ToCopy.rexx script.


A bit more information on installing

The line which activate the ARexx script.  First call up the ARexx interpreter 
which then giving by parameter the storage location to call ToCopy.rexx programme.

In opus you most marked the list of options:-

Run asynchronously

All other settings are set to default.

@ENDNODE

